This paper is about optimizing deep learning training on multi-device systems, which is a topic that spans several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the efficiency of training deep neural networks. The second likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper deals with optimizing training on clusters of CPUs and GPUs. The third likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper uses convolutional neural networks as an example of the type of model being trained. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI. The fifth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with optimizing the training of neural networks.
